CommentType.Title: Fault Report (Notice To Users And Operator)

UserComments.Comment: The "functioning" rapid had no power yesterday, although there was a car plugged in when I arrived. The 22kW units were working fine.

CommentType.Title: Fault Report (Notice To Users And Operator)

UserComments.Comment: Both fast chargers not currently working.

As already noted fast charger very slow. Spoke to a chap who was their inspecting works to the left of charger. He informed me it had been fitted incorrectly and workman would be correcting it in the near future. So hopefully the fast charger will be a fast charge when maintenance carried out.

As others report only one rapid working. The working rapid has a screen fault. No display. Works with normal process of swiping card and pressing start. Note that power cabinets nearby are currently being dug up so hopefully repairs are happening now
Screen completely white, but charger still works. Present card, wait for beep and press 'start'
Still only one working rapid.
One of the rapids still doesn't work. Good 22kw chargers for zoe though. Theres also a MacDonalds nearby.
Working well - CHAdeMO charge.

CommentType.Title: Fault Report (Notice To Users And Operator)

UserComments.Comment: Used several times previously but on 28/6 it suddenly stopped and appeared to have lost all power.
Charged a Nissan Leaf at one of the Rapid chargers at the Broxden Park and ride, 12th April 2015 at 830ish. The second rapid charger at the site is still offline.
Charged successfully using Fast Charger. One rapid charger unit still non-operational, condensation inside display. Such a waste.
Reported in December that CCS connection failed to deliver charge. Council aware and investigating.
Charged using fast charger. 240v/20A 3 phase
The three dual eVolt fast chargers appear to be operational. Only one rapid charger unit operational. Charged successfully using 22kW fast charger.
